Commentary Text: Livingstone to Powell, out Caught by Dhawan!! Good old part-time leg-spin. Good old bowling-to-the-ego. Surely Powell can't block them any longer. And so he clears out his front leg, slogs blindly, but the ball spins big, gets the top-edge, and balloons away towards long-off, where Dhawan runs in, keeping his eyes intact, and finishing it off with the thigh-slap. Powell c Dhawan b Livingstone 2(6)

Commentary Text: Livingstone to Warner, out Caught by Rahul Chahar!! Whoa! What a start! How much did the last second change effect Warner? Opening batters generally want to know who's going to take strike, here Sarfaraz was going to but Warner saw Livingstone and decided he should be the one. Gentle toss up outside off and might have just held a bit, Warner strides forward to drive but ends up pushing at it, slices it to backward point and Chahar takes a simple catch. Perfect start for Punjab Kings as the dangerous Warner walks back for a golden duck. Warner c Rahul Chahar b Livingstone 0(1)

Commentary Text: Nortje to Bairstow, out Caught by Axar!! 152.4kph! Again the short ball isn't all that high, it's higher than the previous one that was pulled away for four, but it's only just above the waist. However this time it comes off a thick top-edge as it rushes onto Bairstow. It flies straight to the fielder at deep backward square and Axar gobbles it up. No celebration from Nortje, his expression hardly changes. Bairstow c Axar b Nortje 28(15) [4s-4 6s-1]
